<p>I have XML file as below</p>  <pre><code>        &lt;MyAttributes&gt;             &lt;MyAttribute User = "CLASS_FROM_1" System = "CLASS1FROM"/&gt;             &lt;MyAttribute User = "CODE_FROM_1" System = "CODE1FROM"/&gt;             &lt;MyAttribute User = "CLASS_FROM_2" System = "CLASS2FROM"/&gt;             &lt;MyAttribute User = "CODE_FROM_2" System = "CODE2FROM"/&gt;         &lt;/Attributes&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The point is I want to check if there are pairs of <code>MyAttribute</code> elements (CLASS and CODE in each pair), for example</p>  <pre><code>        &lt;MyAttribute User = "CLASS_FROM_1" System = "CLASS1FROM"/&gt;         &lt;MyAttribute User = "CODE_FROM_1" System = "CODE1FROM"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p>In case like this:</p>  <pre><code>    &lt;MyAttributes&gt;         &lt;MyAttribute User = "CLASS_FROM_1" System = "CLASS1FROM"/&gt;         &lt;MyAttribute User = "CLASS_FROM_2" System = "CLASS2FROM"/&gt;         &lt;MyAttribute User = "CODE_FROM_2" System = "CODE2FROM"/&gt;     &lt;/Attributes&gt; </code></pre>  <p>XML is incorrect</p>  <p>Is it possible to define such constraint in XML Schema 1.0 (in XSD file for validation)? Maybe changing hierarchy of XML would solve the problem, but I can't change xml structure.</p>